## Symptom

While using `--prelude`, I consistently see the following error.
```
Expected no error, got SyntaxError: Invalid regular expression: missing /
```

## Suspected Cause
If you log out the test contents, you'll find that it inserts `/[HERE]/ Copyright` rather than `[HERE]// Copyright`. This creates a line starting with `/ Copyright`, which is an unclosed regex. Hence the SyntaxError

## Possible Solution
I was able to work around this by modifying `insertPrelude` (https://github.com/bterlson/test262-harness/blob/master/bin/run.js#L194) to slice up to `index - 1` rather than `index`:

```js
function insertPrelude(test) {
  const index = test.insertionIndex;
  if (index === -1) {
    return test;
  }

  if (preludeContents) {
    test.contents = test.contents.slice(0, index - 1) + // change here
      preludeContents +
      test.contents.slice(index - 1); // change here
  }

  return test;
}
```

